yk given x and Î˜ at time tk and p(Î˜, x|Yk ) represents the joint posterior pdf of x and Î˜ at time tk given all previous
observations, including yk . Furthermore, p(yk ) is the total probability of observation at time tk which can be evaluated
as follows:
